v2x_polyarchy.name: Electoral Democracy
v2x_polyarchy.description: Measures responsiveness of rulers to citizens through electoral competition, free and fair elections, and freedom of association

v2x_libdem.name: Liberal Democracy
v2x_libdem.description: Combines electoral democracy with rule of law, civil liberties, independent judiciary, and limits on executive power

v2x_partipdem.name: Participatory Democracy
v2x_partipdem.description: Emphasizes citizen participation beyond elections: civil society, direct democracy, local government

v2x_delibdem.name: Deliberative Democracy
v2x_delibdem.description: Emphasizes reasoned debate, justification of decisions, and respect for counterarguments in political discourse

v2x_egaldem.name: Egalitarian Democracy
v2x_egaldem.description: Focus on equal distribution of political power and resources across social groups

v2xel_frefair.name: Clean Elections
v2xel_frefair.description: Electoral integrity - free and fair elections without fraud, intimidation, or irregularities

v2x_rule.name: Rule of Law
v2x_rule.description: Transparent, predictable, and impartially enforced laws that apply equally to all

v2x_jucon.name: Judicial Constraints
v2x_jucon.description: Extent to which executive power is constrained by an independent judiciary

v2x_corr.name: Political Corruption
v2x_corr.description: Corruption in public sector, executive, legislature, and judiciary

v2x_civlib.name: Civil Liberties
v2x_civlib.description: Personal freedoms including movement, religion, expression, and personal autonomy

v2x_freexp_altinf.name: Freedom of Expression
v2x_freexp_altinf.description: Freedom of expression and access to alternative sources of information

v2x_clphy.name: Physical Integrity
v2x_clphy.description: Freedom from political killings, torture, and physical violence by the state

v2x_clpriv.name: Private Liberties
v2x_clpriv.description: Freedom from government interference in private life, property rights

v2x_gender.name: Women's Empowerment
v2x_gender.description: Women's political empowerment including civil liberties, participation, and representation

v2xcs_ccsi.name: Civil Society
v2xcs_ccsi.description: Strength and independence of civil society organizations

v2xeg_eqdr.name: Equal Distribution
v2xeg_eqdr.description: Equal distribution of political power across social groups

v2xme_altinf.name: Media Freedom
v2xme_altinf.description: Availability of alternative sources of information and media independence

v2x_freexp.name: Freedom of Expression (narrow)
v2x_freexp.description: Freedom of academic and cultural expression, discussion of political issues
